# App Architecture Redesign Plan

This document outlines the approach to refactoring the Investment Advisor multi-agent system. The goal is to remove the real estate domain, split the stocks and funds domain into Turkish and Global categories, redesign the discussion agents using a Mixture of Experts approach with randomized aggression levels, simplify the data flow to the final decider, and integrate a newly defined financial data pool.

## User Review Required
> [!IMPORTANT]
> The user requested that we modify definition documents and prompts first, and wait before modifying the system code. I will complete Phase 1 and Phase 2, then wait for your approval before proceeding to Phase 4 (Code rewriting).
> How would you prefer us to manage the financial tracker script? Should I write that standalone script now or wait for the system code update phase?

## Proposed Changes

### 1. Document definition updates
We will modify the core text files to reflect the new state of the system:
#### [MODIFY] [Investment Analyst App Definition.txt](file:///c:/investment%20advisor/Investment%20Analyst%20App%20Definition.txt)
Remove real estate mentions. Document the Global vs Turkish differentiation for stocks and funds. Document the dynamically generated discussion agents and their aggression scope. Document the financial table generation criteria.
#### [MODIFY] [Investment Analyst App Structure.txt](file:///c:/investment%20advisor/Investment%20Analyst%20App%20Structure.txt)
Remove references to Real Estate. Describe the 9 combined research agents for Gold, Global Stocks, Turkish Stocks. Describe the unified Discussion Agent Template. Describe the `portfolio` isolation and `yfinance` pool addition.

---

### 2. Prompts Reshuffling
We will rewrite the prompt architecture to remove Real Estate and focus more on comprehensive equity markets and expert mixtures:
#### [DELETE] Real Estate Prompts (`1A`, `1B`, `1C`)
#### [MODIFY] Gold & Silver Prompts (`2A`, `2B`, `2C` -> `1A`, `1B`, `1C`)
#### [NEW] Global Stocks & Funds Prompts (`2A`, `2B`, `2C`)
Using global web search contexts, evaluating holdings of funds to treat them as conservative stock components.
#### [NEW] Turkish Stocks & Funds Prompts (`3A`, `3B`, `3C`)
Using Turkish web sources, focusing strictly on BIST criteria and the local market.
#### [DELETE] Old Discussion Agents (`Discussion Agent 1`, `2`, `3`)
#### [NEW] Discussion Agent Template
A single template where `{aggression_level}` and `{conservative_vs_risk_definition}` will be injected dynamically.
#### [MODIFY] Decider Agent
Needs to incorporate memory of past recommendations versus actual execution outcome, receive only Discussion Agent outputs (ignoring Research outputs directly), incorporate Financial Pool Data, and prioritize long-term consistency.

---

### 3. Repository Maintenance
#### [MODIFY] [.gitignore](file:///c:/investment%20advisor/.gitignore)
Explicitly ignore the `portfolio/` directory.
#### [MODIFY] [README.md](file:///c:/investment%20advisor/README.md)
Update instructions for the user to duplicate and build their own portfolio structure.

---

### 4. Code Implementation (To Be Done After Prompt Approvals)
Changes will apply across the board:
- `yfinance` integration for Shariah/BIST/MSCI compliant stocks (evaluating ebitda_ev, ep_ttm, bp_ttm, cfp_ttm, roe, roe_stability, revenue_ttm_yoy_growth, net_profit_ttm_yoy_growth, residual_volatility, liquidity_turnover_weighted).
- Refactoring `discussion_agent.py` to instantiate `N` number of agents, each randomizing an aggression property 0-1, iterating only once.
- Refactoring [main.py](file:///c:/investment%20advisor/main.py) parameters and `decider_agent.py` pipeline flow.

## Verification Plan
### Automated Tests
- Run `python main.py --research-only` followed by discussion-only to observe the new prompts at work.
- Validate `yfinance` queries to ensure all metrics map properly and gracefully handle missing indicators.
### Manual Verification
- Manually inspect the decider output to ensure it leverages memory accurately.
- Verify git status omits `portfolio`.
